Before we start, I clarify some things:
- Django version: `2.0.7`.
- This post won't discuss Django project's structure and other basic stuffs.

## **1. Why use AbstractUser?**

There are some ways to custom (either by substitute or extend) the default Django User model. According to [the Django documentation](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.0/topics/auth/customizing/#extending-django-s-default-user), we customize our User model by subclassing `contrib.contrib.auth.models.AbstractUser` (this will be written shortly as `AbstractUser`) if we 
